comments:
Created 1.4.1974 by renaming the parish of New Hunstanton. See 
    also Table 2, notes (f) amd (h).

Created 1.4.1935 out of the parishes of St. Margaret, South Lynn, 
    Gawood, West Lynn, North Lynn and North Runcton. Abolished 1.4.1974 to become 
    the West Norfolk unparished area.

Created 14.5.1981 by renaming the West Norfolk unparished 
    area. See also Table 2, note (h).

Created 1.4.1974 by renaming the parish of Hunstanton. See 
    also Table 2, note (h).

Abolished 1.4.1935 and divided between the parishes of King's Lynn 
    and Clenchwarton.
Abolished 1.4.1935 and added to the parish of King's Lynn.

Created 1.4.1988 out of the parishes of Walpole St. Andrew and 
    Walpole St. Peter. See also Table 2, note (h).

Created 1.4.1988 out of the parishes of Terrington St. 
    Clement, Walpole St. Andrew and Walpole St. Peter. See also Table 2, note 
    (h).

Created 1.4.1988 out of the parish of Walpole St. Peter. See 
    also Table 2, note (h).

Abolished 1.4.1988 and divided between the parishes of Walpole 
    and Walpole Cross Keys. See also Table 2, note (c).

Abolished 1.4.1988 and divided between the parishes of Walpole, 
    Walpole Cross Keys and Walpole Highway. See also Table 2, note (c).

Abolished 1.4.1935 and added to the parish of King's Lynn. 
    See also Table 2, note (a).

Unparished area which until 1.4.1974 formed the parish of 
    King's Lynn. Renamed 14.5.1981 to become the King's Lynn & West Norfolk 
    unparished area.
